This is a common JavaScript build system based on the jQuery's build system.

Features:

	* Checking of js files using jslint.
	* Concatenation of modules into a single file.
	* String substitution of @VERSION (from version.txt) and @DATE.
	* Minification using YUICompressor.
	* Copy/sub optional modules into dist.
	* Copy extra files into dist.


Requirements:

	* Make
	* GNU/Posix like environment (echo, cat, sed, mkdir, rm, etc.)
	* Java - for jslint & YUICompressor
	* Rhino - for jslint


Adding it to your project:

	* Import this whole directory to a sub-dir of your project.

		If you are using git, just cd into your project dir and do:

		$ git submodule add git://github.com/jollytoad/js-common-build.git build

	* Create a version.txt file containing the version number of the project
		NOTE: ensure the file doesn't end with a line-break.

	* Create a Makefile based on the following example:

----[SNIP]----
PACKAGE = jquery-roles

MODULES = \
	roles.core.js\
	roles.keys.js\
	roles.aria.js\
	roles.tablist.js\
	roles.tree.js

OPTIONAL_MODULES = \
	roles.ie6-css.js \
	roles.ui-css.js

EXTRAS = \
	theme

include build/rules.mk
----[SNIP]----

Optional variables:

	* SRC_DIR - the source directory (default: src)
	* BUILD_DIR - the build system dir (default: build)
	* DIST_DIR - the distribution dir - where everything ends up (default: dist)
	* MIN_DIR - where to put minified files (default: ${DIST_DIR}/min)


Usage:

	To jslint and build everything use:

		$ make

	Common make targets are:

		jslint - to run jslint over all MODULES and OPTIONAL_MODULES
		concat - concatenate MODULES and perform string substitutions, creates DIST_DIR/PACKAGE.js
		opts   - copy OPTIONAL_MODULES into DIST_DIR, performing substitutions
		extras - copies EXTRAS into DIST_DIR
		minify - minify the JS files using YUICompressor, into MIN_DIR
		clean  - remove the DIST_DIR

	Example, to jslint and concatenate the main package without minifying:

		$ make jslint concat


This project can be found on github:

	http://github.com/jollytoad/js-common-build

